The paper deals with the problem of approximating edit distance, which is a fundamental problem in the field of combinatorial pattern matching. This suggests that the paper belongs to the category of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also presents a quantum algorithm and a MapReduce algorithm for approximating edit distance, which suggests that it may also belong to the categories of cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.Distributed Systems. The paper uses metric estimation as a key tool, which suggests that it may also belong to the categories of cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.QL (Quantum Physics).
